===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*laŋ||to lift; to raise}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, STEDT), whence {{cog|bo|ལང||to rise}}, {{cog|my|လင့်စင်||elevated watchtower or lifted platform}}.

====Definitions====
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[lift]]; to [[raise]]; to [[hoist]]
#: {{zh-x|揚手|to raise one's hand}}
#: {{zh-x|揚鞭|to raise a whip}}
# to [[flutter]] (in the [[air]])
#: {{zh-x|飄揚|to flutter}}
# to [[throw]] up and [[scatter]] (to [[winnow]])
# to [[spread]]; to make [[known]]
#: {{zh-x|宣揚|to publicize; to propagate}}
#: {{zh-x|表揚|to praise}}
#* {{zh-x|竇 燕{Yān}山，有 義方；教 五 子，名 俱 揚。|Dou of the Yan Mountains had the right method. He taught five sons, each of whom raised the family reputation.|ref=Sanzijing}}
# {{lb|zh|Cantonese}} to [[publicize]]; to make [[widely]] [[known]]
# {{lb|zh|Cantonese}} tending to become known by [[other]]s; tending to be [[publicize]]d; [[obtrusive]]
# [[Yangzhou]]
# {{surname|zh|xlit=Yang}}

